title: For Sale/Trade:   M48BO 'EGYPTIAN' Contract Mauser (Sanitized)
postcontent:
From what I could find out about these rifles, they were made in Yugoslavia and there were only a few thousand of these "Egyptian Contract Guns" produced. The M-48BO, which stands for "bez oznake", meaning "without markings", were early examples of "sanitized" weapons. There are no markings on this weapon except for the serial number. These "BO" rifles were to be sold to Egypt, but the few thousand that were ready to go could not be shipped because of the outbreak of the Suez Crisis in 1956, after which most world armies switched to self loading, semi-auto or full auto military rifles.

That's what I found, but please do your own research. Thanks for looking.

title: For Sale:  AK 47 Gas Block Front Sight Combo
postcontent:
I have made a small batch of gas block front sight combos. These replace your factory gas block and front sight and combine them into 1 unit. This helps balance the rifle out and gives your old  AK 47, 74, Vepr or Saiga a more refined look.

WILL FIT ALL AK PATTERN RIFLES AND PISTOLS

SPECS
These have undergone a full 2 stage nitriding process. Nitride is a chemical process that makes steel rust proof and has an extremely high ware resistance. Nitriding is what is being used in new production AR15  barrels (as opposed to chrome), bolt carriers and Glock slides.
Plainly put, it is the most protective treatment avalible for steel parts and these gas block sights have gone through two cycles of it.

A lot of the cheap surplus ammo is corrosive which will eat up your parts especially the gas block which is where all the gas comes out of. Having a nitrided gas block will substantially increase the service life of your rifle regardless of what you shoot out of it.

This process of nitriding is expensive to do that is why the cost of my parts are priced as they are. If you are trying to build a high end rifle, this part is a must.

INSTALLATION
These parts are a press fit meaning they are very tight fit to the barrel. This is necessary to insure it does not move. 
There is a set screw in the gas block that helps ensure it is aligned while testing. This set screw will hold the gas block in place during operation under light duty. If you dimple the top of the barrel so the set screw has something to fit into that would be ideal and insure it does not rotate if dropped. 
For extreme use and guaranteed reliably I machined two holes in the block so you can pin it to the barrel. If you want to go this route, use the set screw to keep the block in place while you drill the pin holes into the barrel.

$100 FREE SHIPPING

Tyler Lumsden
REDACTED
Text or email preferred

title: For Sale:  AK 47 Front Sight Gas Block Combo
postcontent: I have made a small batch of gas block front sight combos. These replace your factory gas block and front sight and combine them into 1 unit. This helps balance the rifle out and gives your old AK 47, 74, Vepr or Saiga a more refined look. WILL FIT AK PATTERN RIFLES AND PISTOLS Barrel diameter must be 15mm. ONLY WORKS ON 90° GAS PORTS. SPECS These have undergone a full 2 stage nitriding process. Nitride is a chemical process that makes steel rust proof and has an extremely high ware resistance. Nitriding is what is being used in new production AR15 barrels (as opposed to chrome), bolt carriers and Glock slides. Plainly put, it is the most protective treatment avalible for steel parts and these gas block sights have gone through two cycles of it. A lot of the cheap surplus ammo is corrosive which will eat up your parts especially the gas block which is where all the gas comes out of. Having a nitrided gas block will substantially increase the service life of your rifle regardless of what you shoot out of it. This process of nitriding is expensive to do that is why the cost of my parts are priced as they are. If you are trying to build a high end rifle, this part is a must. INSTALLATION These parts are a press fit meaning they are very tight fit to the barrel. This is necessary to insure it does not move. There is a set screw in the gas block that helps ensure it is aligned while testing. This set screw will hold the gas block in place during operation under light duty. If you dimple the top of the barrel so the set screw has something to fit into that would be ideal and insure it does not rotate if dropped. For extreme use and guaranteed reliably I machined two holes in the block so you can pin it to the barrel. If you want to go this route, use the set screw to keep the block in place while you drill the pin holes into the barrel. $100 FREE SHIPPING Tyler Lumsden REDACTED Text or email preferred

title: For Sale:  Winchester Model 67, first year model
postcontent:
1934-1935 Winchester Model 67. Single shot, 27" barrel, chrome bolt/trigger. First year made and only year with finger grooves. Metal and wood are in excellent condition for a 80 year old firearm. It shoots like a laser beam and is hands down the most accurate .22 with open sights I have ever shot. In fact I love the Model 67's so much I have too many of them. These are great guns and with no powder or subsonic ammo it is as silent as a CO2 pellet gun. It will shoot LR, Long, Short, and CB. This is a great firearm for young and old. 

This is a  real deal Winchester. This rifle has gone 80 years and still shoots and looks great. Real wood. Real steel. No plastic. This rifle might even be too manly for some. This rifle will outlast all of us. In fact, when the world ends there will only be cockroaches, Keith Richards, and Model 67's left.

Another great thing about Model 67's is the price. I will be honest and tell you Model 67 prices stay about the same. They range from $100 to $200 on average depending on condition and when made. There are no serial numbers on any of them (all were made before serial numbers were required) so you have to know what parts Winchester used in what years. As such this rifle is $160 firm. Sure you could buy a plastic semi-auto for that kind of money, but it will take all 10 rounds to do the job versus one shot out of 27 inches of steel precision. Plus it will shoot whatever you feed it. Model 67 don't care. He eats anything. $160 folks. Take yours home today.

title: For Sale:  Sonetronics CVC Helmet DH-132B
postcontent:
Military Surplus Helmet, Combat Vehicle Crewman, DH-132B. This is a Sonetronics size medium and it is in very good condition. A local surplus store has one on the shelf that is in very poor condition and they are asking almost $300. This one that is in great shape can be yours for $175. 

The DH-132B was first issued to Tank Commanders and Tank Drivers who normally had their heads exposed and required greater cranial protection. The DH-132B had a heavy outer shell made of layered Aramid (Kevlar) and was consistent in ballistic protection to the PASGT helmet. The DH-132B was eventually issued to all tank crew members as supplies became available. There are kits readily available that will convert the shell to a Special Operations Headset Adaptable Helmet (SOHAH) if you are in to that sort of thing. Otherwise, this helmet is in great working condition as it is.
